article.headline: (12) KANSAS ST 78, SE MISSOURI ST 42
article.story:
SAN ANTONIO (Ticker) -- Nicole Ohlde had 17 points, eight 
rebounds and six assists as No. 12 Kansas State downed Southeast
Missouri State, 78-42, in the UTSA New Year's Classic.

The Wildcats led by just nine points at halftime but held the
Otahkians to five field goals and 14 points in the second half.

Ohlde, the school's all-time leading women's scorer, passed
former Kansas State men's player Askia Jones for third place in
school history with 1,837 career points.

Kendra Wecker scored 16 points and pulled down 13 boards for the
Wildcats (8-2), who have won six straight games.

Kansas State went 0-for-14 from 3-point territory to mark the
first time in 199 games in which they failed to make a field
goal from beyond the arc.

Kenja White netted 12 points and Sarah Costello chipped in 10
for Southeast Missouri State (4-6), which was outrebounded,
59-32.
